                            <comment id="13056970" author="rangadi" created="Wed, 29 Jun 2011 04:21:17 +0100"  >
&lt;p&gt;The attached patch allows globs while registering remote jars.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is implemented in FileLocalizer.java rather than in PigServer.java. That way it reverts most of the changes &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1566&quot; title=&quot;Support globbing for registering jars in pig script.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1566&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1566&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. I think this is a bit better:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;closer to current production 0.8&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;glob could be anything that FileSystem understands&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;locateJarFromResource only looks at resources&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;another subtle improvement is that now a script can register from multiple remote filesystems.. not just the default&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
